Package: corridorkey-resolve-ofx
Version: @VERSION@
Section: video
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Alexandre Mendonca Alvaro <alex@corridorkey.io>
Homepage: https://github.com/alexandremendoncaalvaro/CorridorKey-Runtime
Description: CorridorKey OpenFX plugin for DaVinci Resolve Studio (experimental Linux RTX track).
 CorridorKey is a chroma-key OpenFX plugin that accelerates real-time
 green- and blue-screen keying on NVIDIA RTX GPUs. This package installs
 the plugin under /usr/OFX/Plugins/ and exposes the corridorkey CLI on
 PATH via /usr/local/bin. DaVinci Resolve Studio 20 is required; the free
 Resolve edition does not load OpenFX plugins on Linux. A proprietary
 NVIDIA driver 555 or newer is required.
